The paper discusses a technique for training deep neural networks without the use of minibatch statistics or normalization. This is a topic that is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), neural networks (cs.NE), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and natural language processing (cs.CL). However, given that the paper focuses on deep convolutional neural networks, which are commonly used in computer vision tasks, cs.CV is the most likely sub-category.
